33-34. Vine culture is described by two of its most important details, adligatio and ampusatio, training and pruning. The training of vines on stakes or props was the ancient practice in Lower Italy (cp. Οἰνωτρία, the ancient name sor that country) and is now the rule cg. in southern France and elsewhere. More common among the Romans, aud this may still be observed eg. in Umbria, was the use of elms or poplars for this purpose.
